Predictions (2026–2030):

* Frontier training clusters: 50–200 EFLOPS effective low-precision compute.
* Largest hyperscalers (Google, Microsoft/OpenAI, Meta, xAI, Amazon): 100k–1M accelerators in a single training system.
* HBM per accelerator: 200–500+ GB.
* Memory bandwidth: 10–20 TB/s per chip.
* Interconnect bandwidth: 5–10× today’s levels, making trillion-parameter MoE models communication-efficient.
* Power per AI campus: 0.5–2 GW, comparable to a medium-sized power plant.

